TY  - JOUR
AB  - Recent experiences of England, Sweden, and Argentina under inconvertible paper currencies that popular theories of the relationship between foreign exchange rates and internal prices must be qualified. The usual practice of comparing only the absolute movements of the two variables has resulted in a fruitless and insoluble controversy. When commodity price movements in gold standard nations are also considered, however, some fundamental modifications of the theoretical conclusions which are based largely on the war and post-war inconvertible currency experiences are shown to be necessary. This paper perhaps indicates a means of bringing the major issues into a common market-place for appraisal.
